<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-02-13T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-02-13T09:00:00-05:00" n="219" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d219">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">811.114 St. Pierre-Miquelon/459:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-02-13T14:00:00+00:00">February 13, 1937—2
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received February 13—9:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>204. Department’s 80, February 13 [<hi rend="italic">12</hi>], 5
                                    p.m.<note n="36" xml:id="d219fn36">Not printed.</note> The
                                Embassy has now received a formal note from the Foreign Office
                                giving the assurances outlined in the Embassy’s 132, January 30, 2
                                p.m., and indicating that the decree will be issued without
                                modification. The Foreign Office was requested to endeavor to have
                                the promulgation of the decree delayed until the Treasury
                                Department’s further representation had been received. The Foreign
                                Office would only promise to endeavor to have the issuance of the
                                decree delayed until next Wednesday.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bullitt</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>